  ============================-->
        <section id="about_assessment">
            <div class="container">
                <header class="section-header">
                    <h3>About Assessment</h3>
                    <p>A Self - Assessment is designed to help an Organisation to assess its position on the journey of Business Excellence. It is based on a dip stick approach for assessing Organisations on different aspects that together define Excellence in terms of the Organisation’s capability & achievements. Based on the relative scored obtained the Organisation could assess & gauge its performance with respect to the Business Excellence Model.</p>
                </header>
                <section>
                    <div class="row about-cols">
                        <div class="col-md-6 " >
                            <h2 class="title">Need for Self-Assessment</h2>
                            <p>Currently in the Industry context other than formal & external Assessments, there are limited avenues for Organisations to carry out a quick and cost-effective study of their processes & practices with respect to Excellence Model(s). If the Organisations choose to employ an external agency (ies), consultant(s) for carrying out Assessments the relative effort, cost & time consumed are considerably high. The need for this Online Self - Assessment application was felt when many of our member Organisations approached us & requested for a quick & easy tool to know the status of the Organisation on various facets of Business Excellence.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <div class="img">
                                <img src="/img/about-plan.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h2 class="title">Points to note:</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            The CII Self-Assessment System for Business Excellence consists of 3 Levels with Level 1 as the basic one and Level 3 being the tough one.

                        </li>
                        <li>The Application consists of different type of multiple-choice questions (5 choices) with each choice adding to specified score matrix.</li>
                        <li>The user needs to select a choice for each question in the different levels.</li>
                        <li>The migration of the levels i.e from one level to next would be intimated by the Administrator through electronic communication precisely email.</li>
                        <li>The questions marked with an <b>asterisk (*)</b> symbol should be considered as <b>mandatory</b> question, these questions cannot be skipped in this application. However, the questions without the asterisk (*) symbol can be skipped.</li>

                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="title">A word of causion</h2>
                    <p class="caution-text">Assessments like any other tool or techniques, should be used with care if they are to achieve the desired results. </br> Several cautions are noted below:</p>
                    <ul class="caution-list">
                        <li>Assessments will not directly provide answers. Instead, they will provide information that can be used to make informed decisions. If the right information is not collected, then the Assessment will have little impact.
                        </li>
                        <li>The Assessment will have little value if the Organisation is not committed to acting on the results. A commitment to change must exist in the Organisation. An Assessment should be used to identify areas where change is needed and to facilitate action.
                        </li>
                        <li>The Assessment must be sound and defensible from a scientific and legal standpoint. </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>An assessment should never be seen as an end to itself. Instead, assessments are a disciplined process for continually identifying what information needs to be collected and then using the information to take informed decisions. By providing crucial information on the Organisation’s strategy, assessment results can be used to help an Organisation become more effective.
                    </p>
                    <dfn class="caution-notes">*Please note that the Self-Assessment application would serve as a dip-stick tool and would not be able to bring out the comprehensive status of the Organisation with respect to the Excellence Model. If an Organisation chooses to have an in-depth Assessment, it is suggested to opt for a CII Facilitated Assessment with the Organisation’s resource person. </dfn>
                </section>



