                        <dt>When a Self-Assessment is required?</dt>
                        <dd>The need for a Self-Assessment is felt most when an Organisation wants to introspect itself and would want to understand its relative position with respect to a specific standard or a set of best practices. </dd>
                        <br/>
                        <dt>Why a Self-Assessment? </dt>

                        <dd>The analysis of the Self-Assessment would throw up areas of SWOT (Strengths, Weakness, Opportunities & Threats) across the various business aspects & would serve as a good input for the strategic planning and related outcomes. The Self-Assessment considers Excellence in a broad sense. It also addresses areas such as the effectiveness of procedures, the achievements of continuous improvement in products, processes & services, and the Organisation’s use and development of its people in achieving Excellence. This Self-Assessment also covers the aspects relating to Innovation and optimal usage of available resources.
                        </dd>
                    </dl>
